  "prompt": "Did islam exist before prophet mohmmad?",
  "response": "Islam as a distinct religious tradition began with the prophethood of Muhammad in the 7th century. According to Islamic belief, Muhammad is considered the final prophet in a line of prophets that includes figures like Adam, Noah, Abraham, Moses, and Jesus, among others. Muslims believe that the message of Islam \u2014 submission to the will of Allah \u2014 has been consistent since the time of Adam, but that the final and complete revelation was given to Muhammad.\n\nBefore Muhammad, the monotheistic beliefs that are central to Islam were present in earlier Abrahamic religions, but Islam as it is known today, with the Qur\u2019an as its holy scripture and the specific teachings and practices (like the Five Pillars), was established by Muhammad.",
